  "commentary": "With SPX at 6565.89 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6550 (-9317M) and max positive gamma at 6600 (+4667M), dealers are likely buying this dip aggressively as they're short gamma and forced to hedge mechanically. The massive negative GEX wall at 6550 creates a amplifying zone where any move lower will trigger more dealer buying, while a push above 6600 hits the positive gamma ceiling where dealers become natural sellers. The gex_surge event combined with the extreme negative gamma clustering between 6500-6550 suggests we're in a critical inflection zone where moves will be amplified in either direction.\n\nKey strikes: 6550 downside magnet (dealers buy), 6600 upside resistance (dealers sell).\n\nBottom line: expect volatile swings between 6550 and 6600 with amplified moves if either level breaks.",
